<subSubSection box="[151,923,1663,1688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1663,1941]" box="[151,923,1663,1688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,923,1663,1688]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,923,1663,1688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Why the 
<taxonomicName box="[259,360,1664,1688]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Saxicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syenitica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[259,360,1664,1688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">syenitica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[366,418,1663,1688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
is not a male 
<taxonomicName box="[580,923,1663,1688]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Oenanthe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="picata" subSpecies="opistholeuca">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[580,923,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Oenanthe picata opistholeuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1663,1941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[204,304,1701,1724]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Saxicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syenitica">
<emphasis box="[204,304,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">syenitica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[313,361,1701,1725]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
has shorter, more rounded wings and a shorter primary projection than 
<emphasis box="[1198,1287,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">warriae</emphasis>
, and in these characters is closer to 
<emphasis box="[403,546,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">opistholeuca</emphasis>
than 
<emphasis box="[609,698,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">warriae</emphasis>
. For example, some 
<emphasis box="[936,1167,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName box="[936,1114,1736,1760]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Oenanthe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="picata" subSpecies="sensu">
<collectingCountry box="[936,959,1736,1759]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">O</collectingCountry>
. picata 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1052,1114,1737,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" sensu="lato">sensu</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
lato
</emphasis>
can have p 
<number box="[1300,1314,1735,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.0">2</number>
= 
<number box="[1331,1345,1735,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="6.0">6</number>
, and p 
<number box="[1425,1436,1736,1760]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
can be 
<quantity box="[236,304,1772,1796]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
&gt; primary-coverts, while 
<emphasis box="[606,618,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">c</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[634,663,1772,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="50.0">50</number>
% have no or only very insignificant emargination on p 
<number box="[1288,1301,1772,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="6.0">6</number>
(thus being very close to the 
<taxonomicName box="[348,448,1808,1831]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Saxicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syenitica">
<emphasis box="[348,448,1808,1831]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">syenitica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[455,508,1808,1832]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
). Nevertheless, the 
<typeStatus box="[732,780,1808,1832]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[821,921,1808,1831]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Saxicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syenitica">
<emphasis box="[821,921,1808,1831]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">syenitica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily separated from 
<emphasis box="[1222,1365,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">opistholeuca</emphasis>
by its well-defined white fringes to the inner webs of the remiges, as in Middle Eastern and North African taxa of the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,224,1880,1904]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Oenanthe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lugens">
<emphasis box="[151,224,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">lugens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Moreover, the identity of the 
<taxonomicName box="[687,787,1880,1903]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Saxicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syenitica">
<emphasis box="[687,787,1880,1903]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">syenitica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[796,844,1880,1904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[916,994,1880,1904]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Oenanthe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lugens">
<emphasis box="[916,994,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">lugens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been confirmed by 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" box="[1269,1330,1880,1904]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">DNA</collectionCode>
analysis, thereby comprehensively rejecting the idea that it might be related to 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1032,1916,1940]" class="Aves" family="Muscicapidae" genus="Oenanthe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="picata">
<emphasis box="[928,1032,1916,1940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<collectingCountry box="[928,951,1916,1939]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">O</collectingCountry>
. picata
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
